verbose_text: Not only was the elevated d4E-BP and dInR expression in heterozygous Src42A mutant animals restored to near-wildtype levels, but also the larval size reduction of homozygous Src42A Jp45 animals was dominantly suppressed by the presence of one copy of the dFOXO 25 allele XREF_BIBR in age matched animals (XREF_FIG).
